article.headline: Fla. International 74, Alcorn St. 61
article.story: MIAMI (AP) -- Johwen Villegas scored 22 points to lead Florida International to a 74-61 win over Alcorn State Friday during the first night of the Adidas FIU Tip-Off Classic. FIU (1-2) barely led Alcorn State (0-4) at the half with a score of 30-29. But FIU took control during the second half, outscoring Alcorn State 44-32. Besides scoring 22 points, Villegas hit three 3-pointers and grabbed 12 rebounds. FIU's Dejon Prejean scored 18 points, Alex Galindo scored 16 and Facundo Giorgi scored 10. The top scorer for Alcorn State was Cornell Landry with 15 points. FIU shot 44.3 percent from the field, compared to 35.9 percent for Alcorn State. FIU also did better from the foul line, shooting 66.7 percent, while Alcorn State shot 47.8 percent.
